Privacy Policy for AKU BTech

Introduction:
AKU BTech is an Android mobile application that provides a complete syllabus for BTech courses. This privacy policy outlines how AKU BTech collects, uses, and safeguards your personal information.

Data Collection:
AKU BTech may collect information such as your name, email address, and mobile number. This information is collected when you register for an account on the app. AKU BTech may also collect information about your device, such as device type, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.

Use of Data:
AKU BTech uses your personal information to provide you with a customized and personalized experience. We may use your information to send you updates and news about AKU BTech and its services. Your information may also be used to resolve disputes, troubleshoot problems, enforce our policies, and comply with legal obligations.

Data Sharing:
AKU BTech does not share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes. We may share your information with service providers who assist us in providing AKU BTech services to you. We may also disclose your information as required by law or in response to legal process.

Data Security:
AKU BTech takes reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.

Changes to Privacy Policy:
AKU BTech may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new privacy policy on the AKU BTech website. You are encouraged to periodically review this privacy policy to stay informed of how AKU BTech is protecting your information.

